{"id": "1489858896070967388", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "content": "Heya! This is something that happens time to time. Ace's source sheets don't always export perfectly, and are occasionally missing entire keys. I noticed my repo was missing multiple keys for a couple Astral Reign chapters when we got the new source files, and it was a bother putting them in, and then I noticed the new source files were missing a couple keys from Everburning Vex when I went to compile Tomato's contribution, because my file had the correct keys but the new source didn't have them, so they imported blank!\n\nIf this happens again, please do make a note of it and @ me and I'll see what I can do. It's possible an older version of source may have it and I can pull it from there, but there's a possibility that key's data may be out of date.", "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:27:21.063000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["294245402532904960"], "reply_to": "1489765053677961391"}
{"id": "1489861424078393487", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "content": "ohhhhhh yep I see what happened, this is a case of the latter.\nThe last batch of source files had this key (`AvgDialog_98284_Content_4`,`bBOI`) and so it made it into my repo files, but the latest source file didn't, so when I batch updated my repo, the program that exported the files failed to find any information for that key.\n\nI'm gonna do a little more investigating to see how many of this error there are, and see if I can fix it across my repo tonight.", "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:37:23.787000+00:00"}
